  "summary": "cursed-modules ships install-time host reconnaissance and exfiltration",
  "details": "Package executes install.js via preinstall, install, and postinstall lifecycle hooks (package.json lines 7-9), automatically running on `npm install` without user interaction. The package's index.js, install.js, and recon.js read host identity and environment data (os.hostname(), process.cwd(), whoami via execSync,.env file reads via fs.readFileSync, and a fetch against the AWS instance-metadata endpoint http://169.254.169.254) and transmit the collected data over http.request / http.get / curl invocations. A shipped publish-and-arm.sh script indicates a deliberate publish-and-arm workflow. The combination of automatic lifecycle execution, system reconnaissance (hostname, cwd, whoami, env file reads), cloud instance-metadata probing, and outbound HTTP transmission constitutes installer-side credential and environment exfiltration on `npm install`.",
